UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2562
1 WHEREAS, Jay Hartz, a longtime member of our legislative family and an adopted
2 Kentucky son, whose service, deep institutional knowledge, wisdom, and kindness have
3 earned him a place in the General Assembly's and the LRC's shared traditions, lore, and
4 history of public service, will be sorely missed by both legislators and staff; and
5 WHEREAS, the members of this honorable body express their sincere gratitude to
6 Jay Hartz as he embarks upon a well-deserved retirement, duly thank him for his many
7 years of service to this Commonwealth, and wish him well in all his future endeavors;
8 NOW, THEREFORE,
9 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
10 Kentucky:
11 Section 1. The members of the Senate hereby recognize Director Jay Hartz for
12 his contributions and commitment to the Legislative Research Commission and to the
13 Commonwealth of Kentucky.
14 Section 2. When the Senate adjourns this day, it does so in honor of Jay Hartz,
15 esteemed Director and friend.
16 Section 3. The Clerk of the Senate is directed to transmit a copy of this
17 Resolution to President Robert Stivers for delivery to Director Jay Hartz.
